==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Zymosis
<hw>Zy*mo"sis</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>zymwtiko`s</grk> fermentation, fr. <grk>zy`mh</grk> ferment.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A fermentation; hence, an analogous
process by which an infectious disease is believed to be
developed.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A zymotic disease.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <note>The medical usage is now (2004) archaic. --
PJC.</note> ⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zymotic</ent>⟦br⟧
